  serving size: 507
time required: 25 minutes
---

Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with
@salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim the @Courgette{1} and slice into 1cm thick rounds.

Drain and rinse the @Butter Beans{1%carton} in a sieve.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{3-4%minutes} each side.
Once cooked, season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Add the garlic and stir fry, ~{30%seconds}. Transfer the veg to a #bowl{}.
Set aside for later.

In the (now empty) pan, combine the @Tomato Passata{1%carton},
@Butter Beans{1%carton} (rinsed from earlier), @Vegan ‘Nduja{1/2%sachet} and
@Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}.

> Add less 'Nduja if you'd prefer things milder.

Stir in the @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{50%ml} for the sauce.

Mix well and bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer the sauce until
slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

When the sauce is cooked, stir in the @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{25%g},
@Butter{20%g} and half the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}.

Taste and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} if needed.

Share the rice between your #bowls{} and spoon over the veg and remaining sauce
from the pan.

Top with your courgette rounds and sprinkle with the remaining cheese and
@Crispy Onions{1%sachet} to finish. Enjoy!